"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The code is incorrect because the OneHotEncoder is being applied to the 'city' and 'country' columns, which are both of type object (strings). However, if there were any numeric values mixed in these columns, it would violate the guideline that states 'The passed categories should not mix strings and numeric values within a single feature'. In this case, the data is fine, but if the data were to change in the future, it could lead to issues. To ensure compliance with the guideline, it is better to explicitly check the data types before applying OneHotEncoder.\", \"patch\": \"12a13,14\\n> # Ensure that categorical features do not mix strings and numeric values\\n> if not all(X[cat].dtype == 'object' for cat in categorical_features):\\n>     raise ValueError('Categorical features must be of type object')\\n\"}"